
Ruby script to generate InterchangeStudentAssessment.xml data from .CSV file
Created J. Hinsdale, 20Feb2013, first draft in Python, converted to Ruby on 24Feb2013
Wireless Generation Megatron Team, Jersey City, NJ

TO USE:
Run "gen.rb" and redirect output to the described XML file name

The output XML is of the form
    header
	templates
    footer

HOW IT WORKS:

Constant markup is in the file "template.xml" which has placeholder
tokens into which values are substituted.

Each line in the .CSV input file expands to an XML entity output for
each of the repeating pairs of trailing columns (level, score)

SUMMARY OF FILES IN THIS DIRECTORY:

File 	    	      	       		            Purpose
-------------------------------------------------   --------------------------------------------------------
README	    	                                    This file
doc.txt						    Summary of .CSV column headers
gen.rb						    Generator script
header.xml					    Static XML markup
footer.xml	      				    ""
template.xml					    ""
input.csv					    Actual input to gen.rb (with newlines fixed)
inBloom data - Reading 3D final.csv		    Data provided to the team, basis for input.csv above 
inBloomData-KB_with_ids.csv	       	       	    Data used to create above map
student_map.rb					    Map of student name to ID
admindate_map.rb				    Map school-year/period/test-type to admin date
level_color_map.rb				    Map test score level to color
*.py						    Old Python code, deprecated
InterchangeStudentAssessment-DIBELS_Next-Matt.xml   Reference output data for checking
InterchangeStudentAssessment-TRC-Others.xml	    ""
